The paper discusses cyber security in intelligent connected vehicles, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). It also mentions the software vulnerability detection and malware detection, which are related to software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the architecture of next-generation vehicles, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The security of inter-vehicle communications is related to cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). Finally, the paper mentions the development of driverless vehicles, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
